The FBI has joined a search for a 21-year-old college student who disappeared from a busy Philadelphia bar early Thursday morning after getting separated from friends.

West Chester University senior Shane Montgomery was last seen leaving Kildare's bar in the Manayunk neighborhood around 2am Thursday and hasn't been seen since.

According to WPVI, the agency has plastered Montgomery's face on digitized billboards across the city offering a reward of $25,000 for credible information regarding his disappearance.

