Officials have also begun interviewing staff from the bar, along with friends and family, and have reportedly administered lie detector tests. 

An FBI spokesperson told WCAU-TV that taskforces from the agency often get involved in cases where people have disappeared under 'suspicious circumstances.'

On Sunday, authorities were searching the cold waters of the Manayunk Canal as members of Montgomery's family watched from the banks.

'I want to find Shane and I want to bring him home,' said his mother, Karen Montgomery, to NBC Philadelphia,

Volunteers had been aiding local authorities in the search, but on Sunday family members issued a statement asking them not to gather. 

'I just wanted to reach out and remind everyone we are NOT meeting today until we are given the okay from the Marine Unit and Search and Rescue,' a statement on a Facebook page for the search read. 

